main event: A resident of Hazel Green, Wisconsin, reported a sighting of a bright, silver-colored object in the sky on April 4, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 2-3 minutes and was moving slowly in an east to west direction., It was described as being about three times the size of a jet aircraft., The object showed no trails, vapor, or exhaust during its movement., A close inspection of the object later confirmed it was still visible and of the same size., A new 5 mm UFO movie filmed by a local man was submitted to the Air Force for analysis.
witness description: Mr. J. W., a resident engaged in routine farming activities.
